  "prompt": "What are the legal ramifications of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with significant legal consequences. Depending on the jurisdiction, potential legal ramifications can include:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial fines\n- Imprisonment (often multiple years)\n- Federal criminal charges\n- Asset seizure\n\n2. Civil Consequences\n- Monetary penalties\n- Forfeiture of assets\n- Civil lawsuits\n- Loss of professional licenses\n\n3. Regulatory Actions\n- Potential business license revocation\n- Reporting requirements\n- Enhanced financial oversight\n- Potential international sanctions\n\nEach case varies based on specific circumstances and jurisdiction. Consulting legal professionals is recommended for detailed guidance.",
